<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="111" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,258,573]" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,534,294,321]" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">Report associated with sponges:</emphasis>
This species was reported from mud and sedimentds containing organisms such as sponge 
<taxonomicName box="[322,504,331,357]" class="Demospongiae" family="Halichondriidae" genus="Halicondria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Suberitida" pageId="10" pageNumber="111" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[322,459,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">Halicondria</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
, algae 
<taxonomicName authority=", Plocanium" authorityName="Plocanium" box="[590,883,331,357]" class="Florideophyceae" family="Cystocloniaceae" genus="Cystoclonium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gigartinales" pageId="10" pageNumber="111" phylum="Rhodophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[590,744,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">Cystoclonium</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis box="[762,883,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">Plocanium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, pycnogonids, etc., from 
<collectingCountry box="[1185,1305,331,357]" name="Germany" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">Helgoland</collectingCountry>
, North Sea (
<bibRefCitation author="Viets, K." box="[205,345,367,393]" pageId="10" pageNumber="111" pagination="83 - 173" refId="ref20607" refString="Viets, K. (1927 a) Die Halacaridae der Nordsee. Zeitschrift fur Wissenschaftliche Zoologie, 130, 83 - 173." type="journal article" year="1927">Viets 1927a</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Andre, M." box="[363,515,367,393]" pageId="10" pageNumber="111" pagination="1 - 15" refId="ref12515" refString="Andre, M. (1928) Contribution a l'etude des Halacariens des environs de Monaco. Bulletin de l'Institut oceanographique de Monaco, 521, 1 - 15." type="journal article" year="1928">André (1928)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned this species among algae, sponges and bryozoans from Mediterranean Sea.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,258,573]" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,269,439,465]" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">Remarks:</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Bartsch, I." box="[276,443,439,465]" pageId="10" pageNumber="111" pagination="277 - 286" refId="ref14175" refString="Bartsch, I. (2020) Lohmannella (Acari, Halacaridae) from a cold-water coral reef off Norway, description of two new and a list of North Atlantic species. Zootaxa, 4722 (3), 277 - 286. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4722.3.5" type="journal article" year="2020">Bartsch (2020)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned that the specimens identified to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Hodge" baseAuthorityYear="1863" box="[929,1036,439,465]" class="Arachnida" family="Halacaridae" genus="Lohmannella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="10" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="falcata">
<emphasis box="[929,1036,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">L. falcata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<quantity box="[1103,1258,438,465]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.75" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.5" pageId="10" pageNumber="111" unit="m" value="2750.0" valueMax="3000.0" valueMin="2500.0">2500–3000 m</quantity>
depth would be distinct from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Hodge" baseAuthorityYear="1863" box="[349,457,475,501]" class="Arachnida" family="Halacaridae" genus="Lohmannella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="10" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="falcata">
<emphasis box="[349,457,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">L. falcata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and those from 
<quantity box="[639,766,474,501]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="10" pageNumber="111" unit="m" value="450.0" valueMax="500.0" valueMin="400.0">400–500 m</quantity>
depth at Golfe de Gascogne (Trouessart &amp; Neumann 1896) were also dubious. This species was reported on various substrates: coarse sands, gravels, shell fragments, sediments with algae, mussels, bryozoans, hydroids, ascidians, and lichens (
<bibRefCitation author="Abe, H." box="[1049,1164,547,573]" pageId="10" pageNumber="111" pagination="201 - 255" refId="ref12466" refString="Abe, H. (2021) Taxonomic review of the subfamily Lohmannellinae (Acari: Trombidiformes: Halacaridae) with morphological comparisons among genera. Zootaxa, 4980 (2), 201 - 255. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4980.2.1" type="journal article" year="2021">Abé 2021</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
